    "problemStatement": "Number of primes in the prefix sum\n\nGiven an array arr[] of N integers, the task is to count the number of primes in the prefix sum array of the given array.\n\nExamples:\n\nInput: arr[] = {1, 4, 8, 4}\n\nOutput: 3\n\nExplanation:\n\nThe prefix sum array is {1, 5, 13, 17}\n\nFor 1 there is no prefix , hence it is 1.\n\nIn the second index if we add 1 & 4 , we will get 5.\n\nFor third index the previous updated sum is 5 and the current value is 8,hence the current index is updated with 13.\n\nFor the last index, current values is 4 and previous sum is 13, so the sum is 17\n\nand the three primes are 5, 13 and 17.",
    "constraints": [
      "1 <= N <= 1000",
      "1 <= arr[i] <= 10000"
    ],
    "inputFormat": "First line has the number of elements and the line contains the set of integers delimited by space",
    "outputFormat": "Print the count\n\nSample Input:",
